Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 809 \N"The Kamaitachi Inn (Part 2)"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.78,0:00:07.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Invited by Hattori Heiji, we came to \Na famous hot spring inn in Nagano.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.48,0:00:12.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In the storehouse of the inn, \NHattori, Kogoro-no-occhan,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.82,0:00:18.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}and inn guest Koyanagi Midori-san \Nwere cut by something sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.12,0:00:19.87,Midori,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Koyanagi Midori (26)\NWriter
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.74,0:00:19.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.01,0:00:23.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.12,0:00:31.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,With the same feelings we've \Nalways held still in our hearts,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.82,0:00:34.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,we fly powerfully into our twentieth year.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.06,0:00:37.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The duo's deduction reveals the identity \Nof the kamaitachi who runs on water.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.22,0:00:41.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth with the \Nbody of a child and the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.57,0:00:43.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.37,0:02:31.01,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,The Kamaitachi Inn\N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.88,0:02:28.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,“The Kamaitachi Inn, Part Two!”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.35,0:02:33.50,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.76,0:02:35.08,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.08,0:02:37.01,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't enter the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.26,0:02:43.01,Bonzo,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Ono Bonzo (72)\NLadylady's Father-in-Law
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.20,0:02:39.70,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}He's already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.08,0:02:46.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Since rigor mortis hasn't set in yet, it's \Nbeen less than thirty minutes since he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.42,0:02:48.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But what's this sickle doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.74,0:02:51.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I thought the Gunma Police were examining it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.00,0:02:56.01,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Since we didn't find any blood \Nwhen we examined it earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.01,0:02:57.60,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was unrelated to the case
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.60,0:03:01.91,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,so I put it back in the storehouse \Nand sent forensics home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.45,0:03:07.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So the culprit could have \Ntaken this sickle at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.38,0:03:09.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Something's not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.08,0:03:10.87,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.20,0:03:15.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This sliding door was cut by the sickle \Nsticking out of the old man, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.55,0:03:17.67,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.26,0:03:21.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then why is there blood above the cut?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.27,0:03:24.79,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,A person's bound to bleed if you cut them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.79,0:03:28.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But, if there's blood on the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.06,0:03:32.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,that means he stabbed the old \Nman before cutting the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.95,0:03:36.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and then stabbed the old man again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.35,0:03:38.34,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.34,0:03:39.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's an act.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.96,0:03:44.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,To make it look like the kamaitachi did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.69,0:03:45.41,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,In that case,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.38,0:03:49.30,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,was preventing the lights from \Nturning on part of the act, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.82,0:03:52.54,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,The annex's breakers were switched off,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.02,0:03:56.42,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,and there were strange marks \Nleft where the culprit entered.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.69,0:03:58.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Strange marks?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.26,0:03:59.21,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.08,0:04:04.55,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,This is probably where the culprit entered.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.89,0:04:06.71,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,The glass is broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.31,0:04:09.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So, where are these strange marks?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.61,0:04:13.52,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Those are my footprints leading \Nfrom the veranda to the fence,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.52,0:04:16.73,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,but see how a shallow semicircle of \Nsnow has been dug out next to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.16,0:04:22.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that because the culprit erased his \Nfootprints with the blade of the sickle?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.92,0:04:27.35,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Even I know that, but the real problem \Nis what lies beyond this fence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.76,0:04:29.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Beyond it? You don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.47,0:04:32.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The outdoor bath?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.48,0:04:36.00,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look. The semicircular \Ndepression ends here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.98,0:04:39.17,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, when the \Nculprit committed the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.41,0:04:45.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He ran across the water as \Nif he was riding on the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.07,0:04:48.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I-Impossible. Such a stunt—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.86,0:04:50.42,DCMain,NAKAMA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I-It's the kamaitachi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.05,0:04:52.56,Daigo,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Nakama Daigo (35)\NWriter
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.42,0:04:52.56,DCMain,NAKAMA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}There really is a kamaitachi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.14,0:04:54.56,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.01,0:04:59.56,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,This must be some kind of trick of \Na flesh-and-blood human, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.23,0:05:02.07,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The kamaitachi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.24,0:05:04.08,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,The kamaitachi appeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.08,0:05:05.45,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Is it true, Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.30,0:05:07.57,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.77,0:05:09.78,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Yamamura just came here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.78,0:05:11.33,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,...and told us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.03,0:05:15.33,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The suspect is a kamaitachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.91,0:05:18.86,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It was just an idiot pretending \Nto be a kamaitachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.86,0:05:23.26,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,But wasn't it the kamaitachi that \Ndestroyed the room we decorated?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.50,0:05:28.43,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,The fluorescent light suddenly shattered, \Nand all the balloons we put up popped.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.43,0:05:29.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,BB pellets.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.59,0:05:30.39,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.60,0:05:33.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There are BB pellets on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.01,0:05:40.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Come to think of it, your late husband \Nplayed survival games, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.02,0:05:41.77,Takami,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Ono Takami (34)\NInn Landlady
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.23,0:05:41.26,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.26,0:05:43.59,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Where is his air gun now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.59,0:05:47.24,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Aside from valuables, all my husband's \Npossessions are in the storehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.56,0:05:51.87,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Then the culprit must have taken it from the \Nstorehouse and shot through the sliding door.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.22,0:05:55.37,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,One of the sections can be flipped open.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.65,0:05:59.92,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But even though there were ten balloons, \Nthey popped at nearly the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.92,0:06:03.02,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,No one could do that in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.02,0:06:05.38,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, with enough shots, \Nyou could probably pop ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.67,0:06:09.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think it was the BB \Npellets that popped the balloons.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.28,0:06:11.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There are only three on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.56,0:06:13.89,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this smell?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.30,0:06:15.92,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.28,0:06:17.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you smell something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.88,0:06:19.53,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.53,0:06:22.36,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,The shards of the light bulb\Nare still on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.94,0:06:26.06,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Shit. My watch flashlight is going out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.36,0:06:28.53,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have to use my phone's light.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.53,0:06:29.78,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Untitled\NPlaying
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.07,0:06:31.16,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing to my Kazuha?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.16,0:06:31.95,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.17,0:06:33.44,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,What about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.44,0:06:37.85,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Not Kazuha, c-cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.85,0:06:41.08,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it smell like \Nsomeone's cooking something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.40,0:06:43.28,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You're killing me here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.28,0:06:44.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.30,0:06:47.81,DCMain,KOHEI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That's not food. That's the smell \Nof a bathroom or cleaning detergent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.34,0:06:50.09,Kohei,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Ono Kohei (7)\NLandlady's Son
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.81,0:06:51.43,DCMain,KOHEI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Also, it was cold because it got \Ncovered in rainwater or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.62,0:06:54.22,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that's right. It got on me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.22,0:06:57.18,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,And the windows weren't \Neven open. Weird, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.45,0:07:02.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, we know nobody here did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.44,0:07:06.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When the old man screamed, we were \Nall standing in front of this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.94,0:07:11.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm impressed you knew it was \Nthe old man just from that scream.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.02,0:07:17.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I just thought it might be and asked \Nthe landlady for confirmation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.43,0:07:20.87,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'd heard a similar scream before.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.18,0:07:23.21,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,When? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.21,0:07:25.86,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,When a TV station came to report on the inn,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.86,0:07:30.22,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,we were offering free foot \Nmassages to our guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.54,0:07:33.94,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,But with the cameras around, \Nour guests declined,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.94,0:07:37.43,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,so my father-in-law had no \Nchoice but to accept a massage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.43,0:07:41.48,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,The way he screamed in pain then \Nsounded very similar to that scream.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.81,0:07:45.17,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,You recorded that program, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.17,0:07:49.13,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. You should be able \Nto view it in the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.13,0:07:50.31,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Take us there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.31,0:07:51.12,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.12,0:07:53.74,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone else stay together in one room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.50,0:07:56.12,DCMain,HAZUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.67,0:08:01.34,DCMain,HAZUKA,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I wanted to tell you, \Nbut this kamaitachi has ruined everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.34,0:08:03.92,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? What did you want to tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.50,0:08:08.46,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Well, actually, the other day on the \NEbisu Bridge in Osaka, he said...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.89,0:08:11.26,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,“What are you doing to\Nmy darling Kazuha?”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.26,0:08:13.22,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,“I'll freaking kill you!”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.46,0:08:17.30,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,D-Did Hattori-kun really say \Nthat to the investigator?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.64,0:08:22.31,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,I might be a little off, but \Nthat's more or less what he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.52,0:08:25.68,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What did Hattori-kun do after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.68,0:08:28.44,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,He managed to throw me off the scent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.99,0:08:32.36,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,But I think Heiji might...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.41,0:08:35.21,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,He might...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.16,0:08:39.53,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Henchman
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.70,0:08:39.53,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Might actually think I'm his henchman.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.53,0:08:41.29,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.22,0:08:41.00,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.54,0:08:45.00,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Masters say that kind of stuff all \Nthe time in historical dramas.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.00,0:08:47.92,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Like, “Don't touch my darling henchman.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.95,0:08:50.35,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.35,0:08:53.34,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think Hattori-kun \Nthinks you're his henchman.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.63,0:08:54.74,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,H-Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.64,0:09:03.13,DCItalic,REPORTER,0000,0000,0000,,This looks like a rather brutal massage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.13,0:09:03.85,DCItalic,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.05,0:09:06.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They do sound exactly the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.21,0:09:10.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, did any of the guests \Nbear a grudge against the old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.41,0:09:15.74,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,He was very generous towards his customers, \Nso I think they probably liked him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.22,0:09:18.51,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,By the customers, you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.05,0:09:23.87,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He was very hard on me, \Nthe waitstaff, and cooks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.87,0:09:29.88,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I heard there was a head chef who \Nhe practically threw out of the inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.21,0:09:32.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember that person's name?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.76,0:09:33.46,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.85,0:09:37.42,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I heard about it when I \Nmarried into the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.71,0:09:40.47,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, they had a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.75,0:09:45.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, do those two \Nwriters stay here often?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.10,0:09:50.77,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Koyanagi-sama comes only occasionally, \Nbut Nakama-kun stays all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.29,0:09:54.66,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, they were \Nboth here that day one year...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.66,0:09:59.24,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,...when Kohei nearly drowned \Nin the outdoor bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.24,0:09:59.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.53,0:10:04.01,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,The storehouse was first \Nbroken into that day, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.01,0:10:10.17,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Between taking Kohei to the hospital and \Nthe police arriving, it was total chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.40,0:10:13.67,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't even have time to clean \Nthe outdoor bath that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.04,0:10:18.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Did they do anything strange that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.28,0:10:20.40,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Not in particular.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.40,0:10:24.72,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Though they do seem a little \Ndifferent this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.44,0:10:28.97,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Previously Nakama-kun didn't have a mustache,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.97,0:10:32.36,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,and Koyanagi-sama wasn't wearing glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.07,0:10:36.43,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't they just have felt \Nlike changing their appearance?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.43,0:10:37.86,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.76,0:10:41.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This snow isn't letting up, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.12,0:10:43.17,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.59,0:10:44.74,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.15,0:10:48.78,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It's been one hour and twenty-eight\Nminutes since we found the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.78,0:10:50.21,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't solve the mystery \Nbehind the trick soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.21,0:10:53.52,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,the snow will change the \Narea around the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.52,0:10:57.27,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know the exact time?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.27,0:10:59.69,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,It was dark for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.69,0:11:03.35,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,My watch is painted with luminous \Npaint that allows me to—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.21,0:11:07.63,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.63,0:11:09.82,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's why they...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.36,0:11:13.20,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Um, this may be a bad time...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.78,0:11:16.44,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,But since it's cold, would \Nyou like some kudzu gruel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.44,0:11:18.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! I appreciate the offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.71,0:11:19.94,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,That would warm us up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.95,0:11:22.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.12,0:11:24.95,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.55,0:11:28.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If you look closely...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.49,0:11:30.35,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,...ghosts are never what they seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.98,0:11:38.46,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Recreate the incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.80,0:11:42.48,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Upon hearing the old man's \Nscream, we came to this outdoor bath,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.48,0:11:45.47,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,which was a shortcut to the \Nannex where he was staying.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.84,0:11:48.98,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,But since we had to cross the \Nbath to get to the annex,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.98,0:11:52.64,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,we decided to exit the inn and come \Nback in through the back door instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.28,0:11:57.27,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, it was after we confirmed there \Nwere no transparent platforms in the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.70,0:12:02.78,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Now let's go outside and head to \Nthe annex through the back door.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.38,0:12:05.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, aren't you coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.88,0:12:09.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No. It's cold outside, \Nand the annex is far way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.41,0:12:10.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.16,0:12:15.67,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,This is how we came to the annex,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.14,0:12:19.67,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,but the breakers were switched off, \Nand it was pitch black inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.13,0:12:24.05,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,When we turned on a light, \Nwe saw the cut sliding door,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.91,0:12:30.56,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,and when we entered the room, \Nwe found the murdered old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.37,0:12:33.55,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,This is how it went, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.55,0:12:35.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.46,0:12:38.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But what is this supposed to tell us?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.16,0:12:40.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it mean there's someone \Nwho could have gotten here quicker...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.76,0:12:43.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...than the people who took the back door?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.64,0:12:46.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.74,0:12:49.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was faster to come \Nthrough the outdoor bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.24,0:12:49.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.35,0:12:51.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The outdoor bath?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.84,0:12:52.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.93,0:12:56.37,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,But your clothes don't seem that wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.70,0:13:00.92,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Did you take off all your clothes and \Nwade butt-naked through the bath?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.92,0:13:02.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,N-No.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.81,0:13:06.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I ran across the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.18,0:13:10.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Can you really do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.22,0:13:10.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.45,0:13:12.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.11,0:13:14.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.44,0:13:18.31,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.47,0:13:20.44,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.70,0:13:23.89,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,H-He just ran across the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.89,0:13:25.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.06,0:13:25.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.13,0:13:29.70,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Th-There must be a transparent \Nplatform or something in the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.83,0:13:33.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, what? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.08,0:13:37.67,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Th-There's no platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.67,0:13:41.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Why is the water so slimy, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.66,0:13:42.67,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It's kudzu gruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.90,0:13:43.64,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.64,0:13:44.75,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Kudzu gruel?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.75,0:13:46.49,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Though to be precise,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.49,0:13:49.55,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,it's in a phase between liquid and \Nsolid before it becomes kudzu gruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.22,0:13:52.39,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It's a phenomenon known as dilatancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.39,0:13:56.56,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,If you apply a weak gentle force, \Nit feels like a sludge-like liquid.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.85,0:14:02.07,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,But if you apply a strong force at once, \Nit becomes rock hard like a solid.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.78,0:14:06.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,As proof, remember how Kohei-kun \Nsaid he nearly drowned...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.31,0:14:09.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...when he tried to chase\Nafter the kamaitachi?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.14,0:14:14.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's because the water \Nthen was the same as right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.16,0:14:16.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's like a bottomless swamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.81,0:14:18.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I-Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.24,0:14:20.75,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,So the culprit came through here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.75,0:14:21.60,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.60,0:14:22.34,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.70,0:14:27.43,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Then they met up with us \Nafter killing the old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.34,0:14:29.01,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.76,0:14:32.00,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,writer Koyanagi Midori-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.00,0:14:32.64,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.64,0:14:33.56,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.83,0:14:38.43,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you switched off the annex's \Nbreakers and cut the sliding door.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.01,0:14:41.33,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be easier for you to meet up with us...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.33,0:14:44.94,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,...if we were distracted by the sliding \Ndoor when we turned on the flashlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.42,0:14:47.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But what about the kudzu powder?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.54,0:14:51.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It would take a massive amount of kudzu \Npowder to make this special water.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.35,0:14:54.86,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,A few days ago, the storehouse was robbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.86,0:14:57.08,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,She must've stolen it then.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.43,0:15:02.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But what was she going to do with all the \Nkudzu powder she mixed into the water?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.37,0:15:04.98,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,The water in this hot spring \Nflows directly from the source.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.98,0:15:07.59,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,With enough time, it would \Nwash away on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.96,0:15:12.25,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Then, the person who destroyed Kohei's \Nbirthday party decorations...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.25,0:15:13.76,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Was Koyanagi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.79,0:15:18.97,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,If she didn't cause a fuss to draw \Nthe cops away from the storehouse,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.97,0:15:21.23,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,she couldn't get the sickle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.60,0:15:25.73,DCMain,NAKAMA,0000,0000,0000,,But how did she pop the balloons?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.73,0:15:27.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,With a water gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.04,0:15:27.69,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.06,0:15:33.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kohei-kun said it smelled like a \Nbathroom or detergent, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.00,0:15:36.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was probably the smell \Nof lemons or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.45,0:15:40.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe she put fruit juice in \Nthe water gun and shot it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.95,0:15:44.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Fruit juice dissolves the \Nrubber used in balloons.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.06,0:15:48.52,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,The missing water gun probably \Nbelonged to your late husband, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.52,0:15:51.60,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you keep it in the storehouse \Nalong with his air gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.60,0:15:52.50,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.50,0:15:53.76,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You may have forgotten,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.76,0:16:00.70,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,but before the incident, someone\Ncut my cheek in the storehouse!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.70,0:16:04.36,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,And I wasn't standing near \Nthe light bulb when it broke!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.36,0:16:09.21,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, couldn't anyone else have \Nperformed the trick you just described?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.52,0:16:10.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Chewing gum.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.76,0:16:11.44,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.76,0:16:14.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You stuck some on the light bulb, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.60,0:16:18.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,While deliberately bumping your head on the \Nlampshade and pretending to be annoyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.04,0:16:23.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,My science teacher said if you stick \Nsomething on the surface of an old light bulb
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.20,0:16:26.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,to create a difference in temperature, \Nthey become prone to shattering.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.29,0:16:33.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, the culprit probably used \NHeiji-niichan's luminous watch...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.62,0:16:38.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...and the light from Kogoro-no-ojisan's \Ncigarette to cut them in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.52,0:16:43.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But why were you cut when you didn't \Nhave anything that produced light?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.73,0:16:45.79,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,B-Because...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.79,0:16:47.36,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Because you cut yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.69,0:16:52.11,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,With a box cutter blade or something \Nsimilar you have hidden under your nails.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.58,0:16:54.09,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You could hide the blood on your nails...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.09,0:16:57.62,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,...by pressing it to your face and \Nsmearing blood on your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.98,0:17:01.87,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, you created the opportunity to\Ngo to the storehouse in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.39,0:17:06.53,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You made us believe there could be\Na kamaitachi and call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.53,0:17:11.88,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Then you used a water gun and air gun\Nto destroy the birthday party room,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.88,0:17:14.38,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,in order to draw the police away from the\Nstorehouse where the sickle was kept.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.80,0:17:21.60,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,When we gathered in front of the birthday \Nparty room, you played the old man's scream.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.70,0:17:25.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,P-Played?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.47,0:17:29.34,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. She recorded the old \Nman's scream from the TV report...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.34,0:17:33.48,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,...with a smartphone or something, \Nand set it to play on a timer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.52,0:17:38.48,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,To finish things off, while we were heading \Nto the annex through the back door,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.48,0:17:39.57,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,she ran across the water,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.57,0:17:42.28,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,arrived at the annex before us,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.61,0:17:45.62,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,and stabbed the old man \Nto death with the sickle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.11,0:17:51.83,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Then she cut the sliding door, switched \Noff the breaker, and met up with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.83,0:17:53.72,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,And if a police officer was among us,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.72,0:17:57.38,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,the police would prove for you that \Nyou couldn't have committed the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.14,0:17:59.55,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Did I get anything wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.79,0:18:03.81,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wrong?! There's no evidence to \Nprove anything you're saying!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.12,0:18:07.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You normally wear contacts, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.19,0:18:09.02,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.02,0:18:12.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The landlady said you weren't \Nwearing glasses before.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.15,0:18:15.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I heard on TV that people \Nwho aren't accustomed...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.88,0:18:19.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...to wearing fake nails have \Ntrouble putting in contacts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.74,0:18:20.36,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.36,0:18:23.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that why you're wearing glasses today?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.78,0:18:28.18,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Which means normally you \Ndon't wear fake nails.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.18,0:18:30.99,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You probably don't have any spares.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.67,0:18:35.71,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Which means it should still \Nbe stuck to your nail.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.28,0:18:40.81,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,The blood from when you \Ncut me and Mori-no-occhan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.89,0:18:47.71,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,B-But why would you kill my father-in-law?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.74,0:18:50.29,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Your chapped hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.29,0:18:50.90,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.22,0:18:53.31,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,My mother's were chapped, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.18,0:18:56.90,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,From being tormented by that old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.20,0:19:04.17,DCMain,YAMAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean the cook who was \Ncruelly fired by the old man was...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.17,0:19:06.87,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. She was my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.18,0:19:08.00,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.30,0:19:11.53,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,My mother started looking \Nfor a new job right away,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.84,0:19:14.89,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,but word had spread that \Nshe'd been fired from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.89,0:19:16.88,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,No one would hire her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.60,0:19:21.19,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,She worked so hard to feed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.19,0:19:23.64,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, she died two years later.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.87,0:19:25.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But why was she fired?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.33,0:19:28.07,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Because the master of this inn,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.07,0:19:31.35,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,who was good friends with my mother, \Nwas offered a marriage proposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.90,0:19:34.41,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The girl was the only \Ndaughter of another inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.76,0:19:38.19,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,If they got married, they could merge \Ntheir inns and expand their business.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.35,0:19:40.32,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,W-Was that-?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.63,0:19:41.64,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.64,0:19:45.83,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,If not for you, my mother wouldn't have \Nsuffered and died the way she did!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.66,0:19:49.70,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You were one of my targets, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.00,0:19:50.90,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.57,0:19:58.09,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But when I saw how your hands were\Nchapped like my mother's, I decided not to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.75,0:20:03.95,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I didn't want that \Nboy who nearly drowned...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.32,0:20:07.22,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,...in the outdoor bath to experience \Nwhat I went through.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.95,0:20:13.48,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean you're the one who sent that \Nphoto of the kamaitachi to the magazine?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.82,0:20:18.23,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I wanted to see if I \Nactually could walk on water,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.74,0:20:21.13,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,and I thought if rumors \Nspread about the kamaitachi,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.13,0:20:26.03,DCMain,KOYANAGI,0000,0000,0000,,guests would stop using the outdoor bath, \Nmaking it easier for me to execute my trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.03,0:20:28.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But why a kamaitachi?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.54,0:20:31.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Because her hatred was driven \Nby her mother's chapped hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.42,0:20:32.12,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.64,0:20:36.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The kamaitachi legend was\Noriginally though to come...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.87,0:20:40.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...from cuts on the skin\Ncreated by the vacuum...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.80,0:20:46.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...in the center of whirlwinds, but now the \Nestablished theory is that the sudden cooling...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.08,0:20:49.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...caused by the heat of vaporization causes \Nthe skin to split open and become chapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.24,0:20:53.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's why kamaitachi legends \Nare common in snowy regions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.01,0:20:57.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I-I heard about it on a monster show on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.35,0:22:21.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.39,0:22:24.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,As promised, I erased the audio file.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.53,0:22:25.90,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,File Deleted
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.83,0:22:25.90,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.10,0:22:28.42,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You're such a good kid, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.42,0:22:29.42,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.42,0:22:30.18,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.18,0:22:31.78,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I heard from Kazuha-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.22,0:22:36.03,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You said, “What are you \Ndoing to my Kazuha?” right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.03,0:22:38.04,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,This again?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.82,0:22:43.16,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't “my,” it was “you bastard.”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.16,0:22:46.92,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I said, “You bastard, what \Nare you doing to her?”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.92,0:22:48.05,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.26,0:22:51.76,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha's like a darling little sister to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.15,0:22:55.08,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,My... You bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.51,0:22:57.01,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.39,0:23:00.04,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Heiji, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.04,0:23:01.23,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.36,0:23:02.06,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}K-Kazuha-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.23,0:23:02.80,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It takes one to know one!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.80,0:23:04.23,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot, idiot, idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.23,0:23:06.15,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,You're an idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.29,0:23:12.20,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo got to confess in \Nfront of Big Ben in London.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.57,0:23:17.70,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I can't accept that I said something \Nso important on the Ebisu Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.35,0:23:26.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, the kids in the Detective \NBoys copied that audio file.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.06,0:23:26.75,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.14,0:23:29.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara uses it as her ringtone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.40,0:23:32.97,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,H-Her ringtone?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.32,0:23:35.97,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing to my Kazuha?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.43,0:23:38.97,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing to my Kazuha?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.48,0:23:42.06,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing to my Kazuha?!
